 Laragh House in Roscommon is 300 years old / For less than half of the price of a two-bedroom apartment in Dublin 1 comes Laragh House at Ballintubber in Roscommon, a 300-year-old three-storey detached home of 4,000 sq ft with a five acres of land and a courtyard to the rear. This house has six bedrooms, with a dessing room, ensuite and viewing balcony off the master chamber. The house is 9km from Castlerea and 22km from Roscommon Town. The selling agent is Property Partners Earley. 4. A detached period house in Carlingford - guiding €225,000 





 
