The old Parochial House in Co Clare
      
Close
 The old Parochial House in Co Clare / Spanning 3,132 sq ft, the Old Parochial House at Kilmihil in Co Clare has three reception rooms and seven bedrooms, five of which are ensuite. This period house was constructed in the 1870s and has been restored comprehensively in recent years. It includes gardens of 1.38 acres and is located close to Doonbeg on the Wild Atlantic Way tourist trail. The agent is Property Partners Earley. 6. A Williamite-era eight-bed in Athlone - €299,000 





 
